ance quickly, without opening the edit form. How?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Click the asset row, then click the Maintenance status button on the detail panel","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Right-click the row and choose Set Status → Maintenance"},{"id":"c","text":"You have to open the edit form to change status"},{"id":"d","text":"Drag the asset row to the Maintenance section of the table"}],"explanation":"The detail panel has quick status buttons. Click the row to open it, then click Maintenance to change the status right away."},{"id":"as8","text":"What happens to an asset's data when you set its status to Retired?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The record is deleted for good to free up space"},{"id":"b","text":"The record is archived and hidden from every view"},{"id":"c","text":"The record is kept with its full history — it just won't show in Active or Maintenance filtered views","isCorrect":true},{"id":"d","text":"Only the name is kept — all maintenance history and details are wiped"}],"explanation":"Retired assets are never deleted. The full record — maintenance history, operating hours, tooling details — stays for reference and compliance. It just stops showing in active filters."},{"id":"as9","text":"You need the serial number of a specific machine. Where do you look?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Admin → Equipment → Serial Numbers"},{"id":"b","text":"Assets → click the machine's row → the Serial Number field on the detail view","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Inventory → Equipment tab → serial lookup"},{"id":"d","text":"Reports → Asset Register → export to CSV and search"}],"explanation":"Click any asset row to open it, and the serial number is right there on the detail view. You can also search assets by serial number in the search box."},{"id":"as10","text":"A forklift was just serviced. Where in the asset record would you see this maintenance event?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"In the asset's Activity Log tab under recent changes"},{"id":"b","text":"In the Maintenance History section on the asset's detail panel — showing the schedule name, date, who did it, hours spent, cost, and notes","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Under Reports → Maintenance History filtered by asset"},{"id":"d","text":"On the Time Tracking page — maintenance is logged as time entries"}],"explanation":"The detail panel has a Maintenance History section listing every past service with the schedule name, date, technician, hours, cost, and notes."},{"id":"as11","text":"You're adding a new CNC mill (type Machine) and want to record what it cost and how it depreciates. Where do you enter that?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"You can't — cost and depreciation fields only show for Tooling assets"},{"id":"b","text":"In the Acquisition section when you add the asset: Acquisition Cost and Depreciation Method, which show for every asset type","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"In a separate Accounting module — assets don't store cost"},{"id":"d","text":"In the Notes field as free text"}],"explanation":"The Acquisition section (Acquisition Cost, Depreciation Method, Work Center, GL Account) shows for every asset type, not just Tooling. A machine, a forklift, or a mold all capture their purchase details there."},{"id":"as12","text":"Your shop has its accounting system connected. How does the GL Account on an asset get filled in?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"It fills in automatically from the accounting system; you'd type it by hand only when nothing is connected","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"You always have to type it by hand on every asset"},{"id":"c","text":"GL accounts are never stored on assets"},{"id":"d","text":"It's copied from the asset's serial number"}],"explanation":"When your accounting system is connected, the GL account fills in automatically. With nothing connected, you enter it yourself."}]}"""
