            Tags = """["assets","barcode","qr","labels","scanning"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Printing & Scanning Asset Labels\n\nEvery asset can carry a barcode/QR label so anyone on the floor can identify it and pull up its record by scanning. The label tools live in a small **Barcode** area on the asset's detail panel.\n\n### Finding the Barcode Area\n\n1. Go to **Assets**.\n2. Click the asset's row to open its **detail panel**.\n3. Scroll past the status buttons — the Barcode area sits there, marked with a QR icon and the word \"Barcode.\"\n\n### What It Shows\n\n- **The barcode value** — the asset's code.\n- **A Copy button** — copies the code to your clipboard (handy for pasting into another system).\n- **A QR preview** — a scannable QR image of the code. (On the asset detail panel it runs compact to save space, so the large QR preview is hidden, but the code and buttons stay.)\n\n### The Buttons\n\n- **Print** — opens the label to print. Use it to put a physical label on the machine, mold, or vehicle. Labels print at the right size for a label printer.\n- **Regenerate** — issues a fresh code for the asset, based on its serial number (or its name if there's no serial). Use it if a code was never assigned or you need a new one.\n- **Generate barcode** — if the asset has no code yet, you'll see a \"No barcode assigned\" message with a button to make one (again, from the serial or name).\n\n### Scanning a Label\n\nForge picks up USB barcode scanners and NFC readers anywhere in the app. On the screens set up for it — Parts, Inventory, Kanban, Quality, and the shop-floor clock — a scan drops the value into that page's search or lookup. For assets the flow is: **print the label, stick it on the equipment, and scan it from one of those scan-ready screens** to jump straight to the right record instead of typing a serial number.\n\n### Why Label Your Assets\n\n- **Faster to find** on a crowded floor — scan instead of reading a nameplate.\n- **Fewer wrong-asset mix-ups** — a scan lands on exactly one record.\n- **Cleaner maintenance and downtime logging** — you start from the right asset every time.\n\n### Good Habits\n\n- **Set a serial number first** if you can — the code is built from the serial, which is steadier than a name you might change later.\n- **Reprint after a rename or a serial change** so the physical label matches the record.\n- **Don't regenerate on a whim** — a new code means the old printed label no longer works; only regenerate when you plan to relabel.","sections":[]}"""
